The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, March 18: The Insurance Regulatory Development Authority (IRDA) today sought to aggressively sell unit-linked insurance policies (Ulips) as an alternative to regular income or pension payouts. The regulator today highlighted the risks and benefits associated with Ulips. Recently the insurance regulator had a spat with Sebi on Ulips.                            
	 New Delhi, March 18: The Centre has fixed subsidy on fertilisers in the range of Rs 23.22 to Rs 26.27 per kg based on the nutrient content of nitrogen, phosphorus and potash, under the new policy, which will come into effect from April 1.
                                                                                                                          
